1. d4 Nc6 2. Nf3 d6 3. e4 g6 4. d5 Ne5 5. Nxe5 dxe5 6. Bb5+ Bd7 7. Bxd7+ $5 ({
Known is} 7. Qd3) 7... Qxd7 8. c4 {White has a plus in the Nimzowitsch Defence.
} e6 9. O-O Bg7 10. Qb3 b6 11. Rd1 f5 $2 ({Preferable is} 11... exd5 12. cxd5
Nf6) 12. Nc3 $1 Nf6 13. c5 exd5 14. Nxd5 Nxd5 15. Rxd5 Qe6 16. Qa4+ b5 $5 (
16... Ke7 17. Bg5+ Bf6 18. f4 {wins for White.}) 17. Qxb5+ c6 18. Qb7 O-O 19.
Rd6 $6 (19. Rd7 $1 Bf6 20. Bh6 {decides the game quickly.}) 19... Rad8 20. Bg5
$2 (20. Qxc6 {wins easily.}) 20... Rxd6 21. cxd6 Qxd6 22. Be7 Qb8 $1 23. Qxc6
Qxb2 $1 24. Qe6+ $5 Kh8 $2 (24... Rf7 25. Rd1 Bf8 {defends well.}) 25. Rf1 Rb8
26. exf5 gxf5 27. Bf6 f4 $2 (27... Rf8 28. Bxg7+ Kxg7 29. Qe7+ Rf7 {tries to
survive.}) 28. h4 Qd4 29. Rc1 Rf8 30. Rc8 Qb4 31. Bxg7+ Kxg7 32. Rc7+ {Pomar
diverted from solid style.} 1-0

